    {
      "text": "Big Run is a rally racing arcade video game released by Jaleco in 1989. Rendered in pseudo-3D, the game is the first to be set in the Paris-Dakar rally raid which the player drives a Porsche 959, resembling that of the 1986 winner. Opponents in the game resemble Peugeot 205 T16s, which went on to win in the 1987 Paris-Dakar rally, with Mitsubishi Pajeros also appearing occasionally.\nThere are two games in the series: Big Run – The Supreme 4WD Challenge – 11e Rallye (1989) and Big Run – The Supreme 4WD Challenge – 13e Rallye (1991, Super Famicom)\nBig Run was also ported to the Amiga and Atari ST by The Sales Curve.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
